            <div class='post' itemprop='text'>
              <p>Some technical details in addition to <a class="mention" href="/u/jesse">@jesse</a>‚Äôs answer: yes, we do sanitize any user-provided HTML  to avoid XSS and other attacks. Currently we use <a href="https://docs.angularjs.org/api/ngSanitize/service/%24sanitize">AngularJS $sanitize</a> for this, which is quite paranoid about all this stuff, so it removes actually almost all tags and attributes. In the near future we‚Äôre going to replace it with something else (probably more configurable) and will allow more features.</p>
<p>Currently you can use <code>class</code> attribute and some common classes from Redash stylesheets (please refer to the codebase for a list):<br>
<img src="https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/redash1/original/2X/0/06256960b4295fb3331d472e157fc19b899ad914.png" alt="image" data-base62-sha1="Sn1ayfWfvv5s5JxMI0vFRkULvS" width="480" height="402"></p>
            </div>

